      "work": [
        "Two-act ballet premiered in Saint Petersburg in 1892.",
        "Based on E.T.A. Hoffmann's story 'The Nutcracker and the Mouse King'.",
        "The 'Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy' introduced the celesta to the wider concert-going public."
      ],
      "instrument": [
        "Struck-keyboard instrument invented by Auguste Mustel in Paris, 1886.",
        "Metal bars are struck by hammers, giving a bell-like sustained tone.",
        "First prominent orchestral use was Tchaikovsky's Nutcracker in 1892."
      ]
